parameters.name: UT
parameters.description: Universal Time given in PDS format: yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:ss.sss.

parameters.name: BX_SC
parameters.description:
The X-component of the magnetic field in the PVO Inertial Spacecraft    
      Coordinate System (PVO_ISCC). This is the component that lies in the    
      sunward direction in the plane that contains the Sun-spacecraft vector  
      and the spacecraft spin axis.

parameters.name: BY_SC
parameters.description:
The Y-component of the magnetic field in the PVO Inertial Spacecraft    
      Coordinate System (PVO_ISCC). The Y axis is formed by the right-handed  
      vector cross product of the X and Z unit vectors where the Z axis is    
      anti-parallel to the spacecraft spin axis and the X-Z plane contains    
      the Sun.

parameters.name: BZ_SC
parameters.description:
The Z-component of the magnetic field in the PVO Inertial Spacecraft    
      Coordinate System (PVO_ISCC). The Z axis is defined to be anti-parallel 
      to the spacecraft spin axis during orbital operations.

parameters.name: BT
parameters.description: The vector magnitude of the sampled field components.

parameters.name: BX_SC
parameters.description:
The X-component of the magnetic field in the Venus Solar Orbital        
      System (VSO - GSE at Venus). The system is Venus centered, with the     
      X axis pointing instantaneously from Venus to the Sun, the Z axis is    
      perpendicular to the orbital (ecliptic) plane of Venus positive 'up',   
      and the Y axis completing the right-handed set.

parameters.name: BY_VSO
parameters.description:
The Y-component of the magnetic field in Venus Solar Orbital            
      coordinates. This component is the right-handed vector cross product of 
      the Z and X unit vectors, and lies in the Venus orbital plane, positive 
      towards dusk.

parameters.name: BZ_VSO
parameters.description:
The Z-component of the magnetic field in Venus Solar Orbital            
      coordinates. This component is parallel to the northwards pole of the   
      Venus orbital plane.
